On the mitigation side, both the US and China are now abundantly equipped with most of the technologies + policy ideas they need to decarbonize.

Neither nation possesses some kind of arcane special secret that could unlock massive added decarbonization in the other country.

But climate advocates shouldn't pretend the world faces *collective* climate apocalypse unless US+China can partner on climate.

It's important to recognize countries are *not* all in the same boat facing the same threats. That helps explain diplomatic stances seen in practice.
